The explosion of APIs, devices, applications, and data sources has complicated the task of building connectivity across the enterprise.
As organizations are connecting to applications outside of their four walls, they risk becoming fragmented. Moreover, existing on-premis
e systems, such as AS/400 and ERPs, need to be able to communicate both internally and externally. Businesses are taking the “best of 
breed” approach, implementing specific applications and services to manage certain departments within their enterprise. Though this
approach provides businesses with powerful tools to run their enterprise, it presents them with the challenge of integration.
